w:r.w:t: Standard Project Management is designed for implementations where full Project Management is required and 2 or fewer solutions are being implemented. All project management services are performed remotely but onsite meetings can be added as desired.

The Cerium Networks Project Manager will become the primary point of contact for all issues related to the solution deployment. The project manager will perform the following tasks as part of the project implementation:
Review and understand the SOW and the business goals of the customer
Make preliminary contact with the customer and review next steps
Create a detailed project plan
Hold a remote project kickoff meeting with the customer and Cerium project team
Place equipment order and provide order status and delivery information to the customer
Schedule and manage Cerium resources
Manage any change orders incorporated into the project
Hold a limited amount of remote status calls with the customer and Cerium -implementation team*
Coordinate the project logistics between the customer and Cerium
Remotely manage the project implementation
Up to one (1) day of remote management of project cutover activities
Provide status updates of first day of business support activities
Comply with customer-provided Change Management policies
Conduct one (1) remote meeting to facilitate handoff to Cerium support
Project closure and customer sign off
*The maximum amount of remote status calls held will be determined by the quantity listed under J91055 in the Cerium sales order.
Cerium Deliverables for Standard Project Management
The following are the Cerium deliverables for Standard Project Management:
Make preliminary contact with customer to review next steps
Provide technical requirements and data collection forms and review for accuracy
Provide relevant project planning documentation to include:
A project contact list
Detailed and product specific data collection forms
Kickoff meeting agenda and minutes
A detailed and mutually agreed upon project plan
Status meeting agenda and minutes
A training management plan and schedule as applicable
Solution and equipment test plans
Provide customer with basic handoff package to include:
A project description and summary document
As built diagrams
All warranty and support information
A post install punch list if punch list items exist
Customer Responsibilities for Standard Project Management
The following are the customer responsibilities for Standard Project Management:
Ensure necessary network requirements
Manage the collection of data using Cerium provided data collection forms
Coordinate and ensure technical requirement compliance
Provide information and guidance on customer Change Management policies
Assist Cerium PM with scheduling and coordinating customer resources
Provide any Cerium requested documentation or information
Provide any necessary access to customer systems
Attend and actively participate in all mutually scheduled required project meetings
Comply with mutually agreed upon project schedule
Coordinate all customer vendors, subcontractors and LEC/carrier interactions
Project Kickoff
The Cerium Project Manager will be responsible for planning, coordinating and facilitating the project kickoff meeting.
The project kickoff meeting will include the following agenda items:
Introduce the team members.
Review Project Team member roles and responsibilities.
Review product capabilities and architecture.
Present the approach, processes and procedures associated with the project.
Review the preliminary project plan.
Schedule team status meetings as required and mutually agreed to.
Review project deliverables.
Review proposed solution.
Review knowledge transfer process.
Discuss Pre-configuration or staging requirements
Review equipment room environmental requirements
Site installation
If applicable, schedule a Pre-Test of customer provided network.
Project Plan

The Cerium Project Manager will develop a project plan. The project plan will define tasks, responsibility for completing tasks, and the project timeline. The preliminary project plan will be reviewed and any changes will be mutually agreed to during the project kickoff meeting. The project plan will be updated as part of the ongoing project status meetings.
Project Control Activities
During the course of the project the Project Manager will manage all project activities to include:
Managing the project plan
Managing project risks
Holding status meetings
Reporting project status to the project team
Managing project change orders
Validating the collected information and requirements from the customer
Managing the installation and configuration to include hardware, software, and services
Project Cutover Activities
The Cerium Project Manager will remotely manage the cutover activities and ensure that any issues that may arise are identified, documented, and addressed.
Project Rescheduling Fees

While Cerium understands that at times rescheduling a project because of unforeseen delays with other vendors, materials, facilities, etc. is unavoidable, it does represent an increased cost to Cerium. For that reason, each customer requested delay without written notice to Cerium at least 2 weeks prior to the scheduled work, may result in a change order to the project equaling the greater of the two options below:
A change order equal to 50% of the scheduled resource hours assigned to the project that are being rescheduled due to customer request.
A change order of $1800
Project Closure and Solution Acceptance
Cerium Networks will seek acceptance from
Account20

for the implementation and document any remaining action items to be completed via the Project Closure Form. The project Closure form will be submitted within one business day after system cutover or production go-live of the solution.
Accou
nt21

will have up to 2 business days to review and respond to the project Closure form, and if written acceptance or dispute of acceptance is not received, Cerium Networks will deem the implementation as “accepted” without exception.
The Solution Acceptance Criteria include:

The equipment, servers or devices to be implemented as parts of the solution or system have been installed, tested, and have passed the basic system or solution functionality tests as defined in the Test Plan.
Solution functions are available at cutover with minimal impact to the users and without major issues.
“Major issues” are defined as the following:
Issues affecting business-critical features or functionality of the solution, which preclude the customer from conducting regular business use of the system.
Issues affecting more than 25% of the end user population.
The solution or system is put into production use by the customer for two consecutive business days.
Project Invoicing
Unless specifically stated otherwise in the customer signed terms and cond
itions, milestone invoicing
may be initiated by completion of any of the following conditions:
Receipt of equipment, licenses, software or other material
Completion of any major milestones as defined in the project plan
Completion of any other milestone as agreed upon by the customer and documented in the Cerium project plan
